Project name:- File Operator 
--> Personal Journal Manager is a simple Python project that allows users to write and manage
 their daily journal entries. The program stores all entries in a text file so that they can be viewed later.
This project is created using Object-Oriented Programming (OOP), File Handling, and Exception Handling concepts in Python.

--> Features:-
- Add a new journal entry with date and time.
- View all saved journal entries.
- Search entries using a keyword or date.
- Delete all journal entries.
- User-friendly menu-driven program.

--> Technologies Used:-
- Python
- OOP (Classes and Objects)
- File Handling
- Exception Handling
- Datetime Module

--> File Used:-
journal.txt → Stores all journal entries.

--> File Handling:-

The project uses file operations to store and retrieve journal entries.

a mode for appending entries
r mode for reading entries
w mode for deleting all entries

-->Datetime Module:-
The datetime module is used to automatically store the current date and time with each journal entry.

--> Menu Options
1. Add a New Entry
2. View All Entries
3. Search for an Entry
4. Delete All Entries
5. Exit

--> Conclusion:-
Personal Journal Manager is a simple and useful application for storing daily thoughts and notes. 
It demonstrates the practical use of Python programming concepts such as OOP, File Handling, and Exception Handling.

